    "summary": "Three Maryland athletes, Haley Skarupa, Thomas Hong, and Noah Grove, are competing for Team USA in the 2018 Winter Olympic and Paralympic Games, sharing their excitement on social media. They express honor and enthusiasm as they prepare to represent the United States in their respective sports.",
    "content": "COLLEGE PARK, Maryland \u2014 Three athletes with Maryland connections are in Pyeongchang, South Korea, to compete in the 2018 Winter Olympic Games and Paralympic Games for Team USA.\nMarylanders Haley Skarupa, Thomas Hong and Noah Grove took to social media to express their excitement for the games.\nName: Haley Skarupa\nSport: Women\u2019s ice hockey\nAge: 24\nMaryland connection:\u00a0Born in Montgomery County, Md.\nWhen she competes for the first time in South Korea: Sunday, Feb. 11 at 4:10 p.m.\n\nTruly honored to represent and be a part of @TeamUSA for the upcoming Winter Olympic games with this amazing group of teammates! What a year. #PyeongChang2018 https://t.co/5c0hBNA2VJ\n\u2014 Haley Skarupa (@skrooops28) January 2, 2018\n\n\n\n\n\n\nTeam processing how do we look #teamusa #pyeongchang2018\nA post shared by  Haley Skarupa (@skrooops28) on Feb 1, 2018 at 7:09pm PST\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nAbout to depart for South Korea special thanks to @bedgear for helping us travel in comfort! #SleepFuels #SleepNaked ??\u2014> ??\nA post shared by  Haley Skarupa (@skrooops28) on Jan 30, 2018 at 2:37pm PST\n\n\n\n\nName: Thomas Hong\nSport: Speedskating\nAge: 20\nMaryland connection: Grew up in Howard County, Md., and went to the University of Maryland for his freshman year.\nWhen he competes for the first time in South Korea: Sunday, Feb. 11 at 3:30 p.m.\n\n\n\n\n\n@usspeedskating landed safely in Korea, and I got to spend a few moments with my dad. Just now realizing that we look like a couple of Korean tourists. #ringstho\nA post shared by  thomas hong (@thomasishong) on Jan 31, 2018 at 2:32pm PST\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nWE GOIN TO THE OLYMPICS BABY\nA post shared by  thomas hong (@thomasishong) on Dec 18, 2017 at 1:18pm PST\n\n\n\n\nName: Noah Grove\nSport: Sled hockey\nAge: 18\nMaryland connection:\u00a0Born in Frederick County, Md.\nWhen he competes for the first time in South Korea: Sunday, March 11 at 12 p.m.\n\nLet\u2019s go!!!!!???? https://t.co/EiCET7T4DF\n\u2014 Noah Grove (@ncgrove_16) January 1, 2018\n\n\n\n\n\n\nWhat a good looking group of guys #roadtopeyongchang2018 #WSHC\nA post shared by  Noah Clyde (@noah_grove) on Dec 11, 2017 at 1:31pm PST\n\n\n\nGet a sneak preview of Friday night\u2019s Opening Ceremony:\n\n\n\n\u00a0\nWhere will you be as the whole world comes together? The Opening Ceremony of the 2018 Winter Olympics. FRIDAY 8ET/5PT on NBC\nPosted by NBC Olympics on Monday, February 5, 2018\n\n\u00a0\nRead more about the three Maryland athletes.",
