    "link": "https://cnsmaryland.org/2017/12/10/war-on-hot-takes-episode-12-season-finale-nfl-recap-ohtani-and-more/",
    "title": "\u201cWAR on Hot Takes\u201d Episode 12: Season finale, NFL recap, Ohtani and more",
    "topic": "Sports",
    "tags": [
      "Dylan Sinn",
      "Adam Zielonka",
      "Capital News",
      "More Mascot",
      "Washington Teams"
    ],
    "summary": "Dylan Sinn and Adam Zielonka conclude their sports podcast \"WAR on Hot Takes\" with a deep dive into the \"More Than a Mascot\" project, discussing its reporting challenges and NFL-related topics. The episode also recaps recent performances of Washington and Baltimore teams, featuring insights from various Capital News Service reporters.",
    "content": "UPDATE: With the addition of a bonus segment, the season finale is now over an hour long!\u00a0Dylan Sinn and Adam Zielonka take you behind the scenes of the \u201cMore than a Mascot\u201d project, which they and other Capital News Service reporters spent three months reporting. Sinn and Zielonka, the lead reporters on the project, are joined by Capital News Service reporter Julia Karron and Capital News Service data editor Sean Mussenden.\nThis is the 12th episode and season finale of Capital News Service\u2019s sports podcast, \u201cWAR on Hot Takes,\u201d with Dylan Sinn and Adam Zielonka. We approach Washington and Baltimore professional sports from an outsider\u2019s perspective and have data-driven discussions.\n\nhttps://cnsmaryland.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/ep12_HOURFINAL.mp3\nOn this episode\u2026\n1:14\u00a0\u2014 Dylan introduces Capital News Serivce\u2019s \u201cMore Than a Mascot\u201d project\n2:12\u00a0\u2014 Capital News Service editor Sean Mussenden joins the program\n4:35\u00a0\u2014 Dylan discusses the California Racial Mascots Act\n5:33\u00a0\u2014 Adam explains the NFL team\u2019s foundation and lobbying efforts\n7:24\u00a0\u2014 Sean discusses the behind-the-scenes of the project\u2019s reporting and editing\n8:36\u00a0\u2014 Adam dishes on how the title \u201cMore Than a Mascot\u201d was chosen\n10:15\u00a0\u2014 What is something Sean would want to do should there be another follow-up someday?\n11:31\u00a0\u2014 \u201cMore Than a Mascot\u201d Julia Karron joins the program\n13:02\u00a0\u2014 How did a quilt factor into the process at Red Lodge High School in Montana?\n14:05\u00a0\u2014 Julia, Dylan and Adam discuss the reporting challenges they faced\n20:20\u00a0\u2014 Dylan owes Adam an apology\n22:28 \u2014 Recapping Washington football\u2019s recent skid and projecting the future\n24:53 \u2014 The Kirk Cousins question\n26:24 \u2014 Adam teases an upcoming CNS project about FedEx Field\n32:27 \u2014 Recapping the Baltimore Ravens\u2019 three-game winning streak since their bye\n34:19 \u2014 Is the Ravens\u2019 defense actually the best in the league? DVOA says so\n36:13 \u2014 CNS reporter Chris Rogers joins the show to talk about Joe Flacco\u2019s career-worst season\n37:35 \u2014 Recapping Joe Flacco\u2019s season-best performance against Detroit\n39:18 \u2014 How well does Flacco need to play for the Ravens to stay successful?\n43:11 \u2014 CNS reporter Daniel Chavkin joins the podcast to discuss his article on Shohei Ohtani\n43:41 \u2014 What was the methodology for Daniel\u2019s article?\n45:36 \u2014 Are the Angels the right fit for Shohei Ohtani?\n48:05 \u2014 Will Ohtani trying to pitch and hit make his transition more difficult?\n49:04 \u2014 How does Ohtani compare to Madison Bumgarner, the best hitting pitcher in the game?\n50:43 \u2014 CNS reporter and basketball enthusiast Chris Miller joins the show\n51:47 \u2014 Bradley Beal scored 51 points on Dec. 5\n59:35 \u2014 Are the Wizards a threat in the playoffs?\n1:02:22 \u2014 A blooper reel of our mistakes, bad takes and awkward moments!\n1:06:39 \u2014 Thank you for listening this season!",
