    "summary": "The 11th episode of \"WAR on Hot Takes\" discusses Washington's playoff prospects, their crucial match against New Orleans, and John Wall\u2019s performance, alongside a Capitals update including Braden Holtby\u2019s milestone and their win over the Penguins.",
    "content": "This is the 11th episode of Capital News Service\u2019s sports podcast, \u201cWAR on Hot Takes,\u201d with Dylan Sinn and Adam Zielonka. We approach Washington and Baltimore professional sports from an outsider\u2019s perspective and have data-driven discussions.\n\nhttps://cnsmaryland.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/ep11_final.mp3\nOn this week\u2019s episode\u2026\n1:28 \u2014 Would Washington be a playoff team in the AFC?\n4:27 \u2014 Was Washington\u2019s loss to Minnesota a fluke?\n6:54 \u2014 Washington\u2019s match-up with New Orleans is essentially a must-win.\n9:46 \u2014 Washington Player to Watch for Week 11.\n11:19 \u2014 Baltimore Player to Watch for Week 11.\n12:55 \u2014 Wizards\u2019 recent winning streak against mediocre teams.\n13:46 \u2014 John Wall\u2019s shooting against Sacramento vs. against everyone else.\n17:30 \u2014 Tom Brady gave John Wall a signed copy of his book.\n19:08 \u2014 What if John Wall played at the same level until he is Tom Brady\u2019s age?\n24:22 \u2014 Chase Pyke joins Adam and Dylan in the booth to talk Capitals hockey.\n25:04 \u2014 Braden Holtby\u2019s recent career milestone and its historic significance.\n25:52 \u2014 The Capitals struggle in the second game of back-to-backs.\n26:46 \u2014 Was the Capitals\u2019 win over the Penguins their best game of the season?\n27:47 \u2014 What do the Capitals need to improve on at this point in the season?\n\u00a0\nhttps://cnsmaryland.org/2017/11/11/carlsons-two-point-night-lifts-capitals-over-penguins/",
