    "summary": "The \"WAR on Hot Takes\" podcast discusses the unexpected performance of the Washington NFL team and issues with the Ravens' offense, while also previewing key players for upcoming games and analyzing improvements in the Wizards\u2019 second-string backcourt. It also explores Nathan Walker\u2019s potential to become the first Australian NHL player with the Capitals.",
    "content": "This is the fourth episode of Capital News Service\u2019s sports podcast, \u201cWAR on Hot Takes,\u201d with Dylan Sinn and Adam Zielonka. We approach Washington and Baltimore professional sports from an outsider\u2019s perspective, influenced by data analytics.\n\nhttps://cnsmaryland.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/WAR4_mixdown.mp3\n0:56\u2013Is the Washington NFL team better than we expected at the start of the season?\n4:23\u2013What\u2019s wrong with the Ravens\u2019 offense?\n8:03\u2013Who are Washington and Baltimore\u2019s players to watch for Week 4?\n12:45\u2013Why will the Wizards\u2019 new second-string backcourt be an improvement over last season\u2019s?\n19:47\u2013What are Nathan Walker\u2019s chances of becoming the first Australian in the NHL? (featuring CNS reporter Chase Pyke)\nArticles Referenced:\nNew neighbors Frazier, Meeks should be upgraded backups for Wizards\u2019 stars\n\nWizards denounce Trump\u2019s remarks on athlete protest at media day\n\nGlobe-trotting Australian Nathan Walker on verge of making Capitals",
