    "summary": "In the third episode of \"WAR on Hot Takes,\" Dylan Sinn and Adam Zielonka analyze NFL Week 2, discussing the Ravens' standing among 2-0 teams and Washington's improved offense, while also highlighting key players to watch in Week 3. They also review the Orioles' season and the Nationals' bullpen improvements with insights from CNS reporter Conner Hoyt.",
    "content": "Here\u2019s the third episode of Capital News Service\u2019s sports podcast, \u201cWAR on Hot Takes,\u201d with Dylan Sinn and Adam Zielonka. We approach Washington and Baltimore professional sports from an outsider\u2019s perspective, influenced by data analytics.\n\nhttps://cnsmaryland.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/WAR_ep_3.mp3\n1:15 \u2014 Where do the Ravens rank among 2-0 teams?\n5:48 \u2013What has been different about Washington\u2019s offense in the first two weeks of the season?\n8:10 \u2014\u00a0Which players should Washington and Baltimore fans be watching for during Week 3 of the NFL season?\n12:30 \u2014 What worked for the Orioles this season and what are their priorities for the offseason?\n23:46 \u2014 How much has the Nationals\u2019 bullpen improved in the second half of the season? (featuring CNS reporter Conner Hoyt)\nArticle referenced:\nhttps://cnsmaryland.org/2017/09/15/a-chance-for-nationals-to-capitalize-on-dodgers-swoon/",
