    "summary": "In the second episode of \"WAR on Hot Takes,\" Dylan Sinn and Adam Zielonka discuss the Orioles' playoff chances, whether the Nationals should rest after clinching their division, the Mystics' path to the WNBA Finals, quarterback salaries vs. performance, and key players for Washington and Baltimore in NFL Week 2.",
    "content": "Here\u2019s the second episode of Capital News Service\u2019s sports podcast, \u201cWAR on Hot Takes,\u201d with Dylan Sinn and Adam Zielonka. We approach Washington and Baltimore professional sports from an outsider\u2019s perspective, influenced by data analytics.\n\nhttps://cnsmaryland.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/War2final_mixdown.mp3\nOn this episode, Dylan and Adam ask:\n0:57 \u2014 What are the Orioles\u2019 chances of making the postseason?\n5:18 \u2014 Should the Nationals rest their players after clinching the division or play for home-field advantage in the NLCS?\n7:59 \u2014 What do the Mystics have to do to beat the Minnesota Lynx and advance to the WNBA Finals?\n14:28 \u2014 What is the relationship between quarterback salaries and their performance over the last four seasons? (featuring CNS reporter Chris Rogers)\n21:35 \u2014 Which players should Washington and Baltimore fans be watching for during Week 2 of the NFL season?",
