    "content": "Capital News Service\u2019s Studio C is proud to debut its newest venture, \u201cWAR on Hot Takes,\u201d a podcast by Dylan Sinn and Adam Zielonka approaching Washington and Baltimore professional sports from an outsider\u2019s perspective, influenced by data analytics. The podcast will discuss newsworthy topics about local sports, consider contrarian takes backed up by data and promote sports journalism published by Capital News Service.\nIn the pilot episode, Dylan and Adam discuss\u2026\n1:32 \u2014 Is Kirk Cousins worth the franchise tag salary he\u2019ll earn in 2017?\n5:57 \u2014 Should the Ravens throw the ball less often, considering Joe Flacco\u2019s mediocrity?\n10:30 \u2014 Who are one Washington player and one Baltimore player to watch throughout the NFL season?\n14:47 \u2014 Is Anthony Rendon getting the attention he deserves in the National League MVP race?\n22:30 \u2014 Why does the Orioles\u2019 low walk rate matter?\nhttps://cnsmaryland.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/First-episode.mp3",
