    "summary": "The CNS team covered a range of major sporting events from the Super Bowl to March Madness, with their top sports stories gaining significant traction on Facebook. One notable story was even published by external media outlets like The Daily Record and The Arizona Republic.",
    "content": "The first four months of the year were jam-packed with sporting events \u2014 and the CNS team has been there to capture all of the excitement. From the Super Bowl, to the Big Ten Tournament, to March Madness, to sports in politics and post-Olympic news, these events have kept our reporters hard at work, developing stories and visualizations for the website and social media channels.\nTo wrap up the semester, the CNS social team compiled a list of the top-performing sports pieces, by category, so you can review what you might have missed.\nNote: One of these stories was even published by other publications like The Daily Record and The Arizona Republic. *Slam dunk.*\nThe most popular graphic\nFacebook reach: 1,194\n\nThe most popular data visualization/graphic hybrid\nFacebook reach: 1,103\n\nThe most popular video/gif\nFacebook reach: 1,026\n\nThe most popular data visualization\nFacebook reach: 760\n\nThe most popular article\nFacebook reach: 448\n\nThe most popular \u201cFanalytics\u201d podcast episode\nFacebook reach: 407\n\nThe most popular graphic and social story\nFacebook reach: 227\n\n*Data as of April 13.",
