    "content": "Gabe and Connor discuss the potential consequences of Rajon Rondo\u2019s injury, jump around the sports landscape for some quick stats, and perform an original song about the playoffs in D.C.\nLyrics: You trudged through months of late-night games against the Nuggets and the Jazz\nYou yawned at the sight of another goal against the lowly Avalanche\nYou smiled after every win and now you think it\u2019s really happening\nThe playoffs are here again, and DC might be a champion\nThrow on your Ovechkin jersey\nIt\u2019s playoff time in DC\nRemember when the Caps were Number One, and lost in the first round?\nWell yes I do, but we\u2019re better now, this time we\u2019ll get the crown.\nRemember when the Wiz had the edge, and John Wall broke his hand?\nThat was a fluke, we\u2019d have beaten them, the Hawks won\u2019t win again.\nI\u2019m betting everything I own on a parade in DC\nAt least until the Capitals lose two of their first three\nPanic goes to overtime after every single loss\nYou resort to cheering losses by the Penguins and the Sharks\nAll six teams from the Great White North lost in Game 1\nBut Maple Leaf wins in two and three are spoiling the fun\nThe Oilers lead 3 to 2, Canada is coming through\nThe Senators up 3 to 1, Boston\u2019s looking pretty done\nCanada\u2019s putting the U.S. on the shelf\nIf it\u2019s any consolation the Blue Jays are 3 and 12\nTHAT\u2019S OUR SPORT\nHey it\u2019s the playoffs\nHey it\u2019s the playoffs\nTo win either title, there\u2019s a six percent chance\nTo pull off both, it\u2019s less than one percent\nBut when neither happens, there\u2019s unbearable misery\nThat\u2019s just playoff time in DC",
